description: Memory reminders for coding and Git workflow in pi-zig-bun
globs: "*.ts, *.zig, *.md"
alwaysApply: false
---

- For future coding sessions, use this project memory:
  1. Use Bun-first command execution (`bun`, `bunx`, `bun test/build/install`).
  2. When choosing tooling for quality checks, use `prek` as the default pre-commit tool.
  3. If exploring external tooling or behavior, sequence is: `search`, `eza`, then `gemini -y p`.
  4. Keep logs for transport/debug off from final code.
  5. Always verify `bunx tsc --noEmit` and `zig build` before commit.